data.title: Beautiful Bell P-39 Airacobra
data.meta_description: The Bell P-39 Airacobra was an innovative US WWII fighter which despite design issues was highly successful in eastern Europe and SE Asia
data.text:
Military Aircraft

The Bell P-39 Airacobra was one of the primary American fighter aircraft in service at the start of World War II. The P-39 was widely used by the Soviet Air Force, and saw action in a number of other theatres as well, including use by the RAF.

The first time I saw one

It was on a beach in Australia, September 2022. An oyster-encrusted wreck, discovered when I was researching Australiaâ€™s role in WWII and ended up in the bomb bay of a B52.

The wreck was reportedly the result of a below bingo fuel episode as the plane made its way back to base at Lockhart River, Queensland.
